3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the implementation of an abductive framework on top of the DLV engine, which is a programming language for logic programming. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper analyzes the computational complexity of the main problems arising in the context of abduction with penalization from logic programs, which is a common topic in the DS sub-category. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the application of abductive reasoning to optimization problems, which is a topic that falls under the SY sub-category.
